events.1910: Brazzaville becomes part of colonial French Equatorial Africa.
events.1940: Brazzaville becomes capital of government-in-exile of France (Free France) during World War II.
events.1956: Moyen-Congo municipal elections, 1956 held; Fulbert Youlou becomes mayor.
events.1960: City becomes capital of independent Republic of the Congo.
events.1965: July: 1965 All-Africa Games held in Brazzaville.
events.1971: University of Brazzaville and Lycée Français Saint-Exupéry de Brazzaville (school) founded.
events.1980: 5 May: Catholic pope visits city. Commune of Brazzaville detaches from the Pool Department.
events.1997: City taken by pro-Sassou Nguesso forces during the Republic of the Congo Civil War (1997–99).
events.2001: December: Trial of former president Lissouba held in city.
events.2002: June: 'Government troops battle Ninja rebels in Brazzaville.'
events.2015: 4–19 September: 2015 African Games held in Brazzaville.
